350003	509	2021-07-30 17:05:24	\r\n1.   Following activities pertaining to in-house development and experimentation were carried out:\r\na.   Control System Designing. Point recommended to be dropped.\r\n\r\n(1)   Control circuit PCB for phase difference detection between two magnetrons has been fabricated. The PCB will communicate the phase detection signal to Single Board Computer (SBC) through ADC. \r\n\r\n(2)   Algorithms are being developed for phase matching of two magnetrons and will be implemented on SBC.  DAC and ADC cards have been procured and tested. \r\n\r\nb.   RF Devices. Following in-house design, development and high power testing of RF devices have been completed. Point recommended to be dropped.\r\n\r\n(1)   Waveguide circulators. Waveguide circulators equipped with biased ferrite disks and high power magnets are used in the project experimentation. Inhouse design and fabrication of 04x circulators has been completed. VNA Testing revealed satisfactory results. The fabricated circulators were also tested at 1 kW and were declared satisfactory. The circulators are successfully being used in experimentation involving injection locking and power combining of x02 1 kW magnetrons. The inhouse design and development activity resulted in a cost saving equivalent to PKR 5 Million. Point recommended to be dropped.\r\n\r\n(2)   Waveguide directional couplers. High power testing of fabricated waveguide directional couplers has been completed. The inhouse design and development activity resulted in a cost saving equivalent to PKR 2.3 Million. Point recommended to be dropped.\r\n\r\n(3)   Waveguide Termination. Design as well as multiphysics thermal simulation of high power waveguide termination based on wedged scheme has been completed.  Point recommended to be dropped.\r\n\r\n(4)   Phase Shifter. IC for a 360o Phase Shifter has been procured, and the PCB has been fabricated. Testing of the phase shifter on VNA has also been completed. Point recommended to be dropped.\r\n\r\n(5)   Power Combiner. An H-plane power combiner is required for power combination of x02 1 kW magnetrons. Inhouse design and fabrication of power combiner followed by high power testing has been successfully completed. The indigenous design and development of power combiner resulted in cost saving equivalent to PKR 0.5 Million. Point recommended to be dropped.\r\n\r\n(6)   Horn Antenna. A high power horn antenna required for radiating the magnetron combined power has been fabricated. The antenna is planned to be tested in an anechoic chamber to evaluate radiation characteristics. Point recommended to be dropped.\r\n\r\nc.   Experimentations.\r\n\r\n(1)   Injection Locking of a Single Magnetron. An experimental schematic was developed to accomplish injection locking of a single magnetron. Experiments were conducted with R&S signal generator as injection source. The injection signal was fed to a free running magnetron through a series of high power circulators, and the bandwidth of the magnetron was observed to reduce within 10 Hz. Experiments have also been completed with SDR B200 as injection source. The experiment was conducted with adequate safeties in place. The procedure and safeties were counter-checked by the QC teams following appropriate QC sheets. Point recommended to be dropped.\r\n\r\n(2)   Power Combining of x 02 Magnetrons. Experimental schematic was developed to combine power of two injection locked magnetrons. The experiment has been conducted wherein power of each magnetron was fed to a waveguide combiner through series of high power circulators and directional couplers. Both magnetrons were injection locked through a 3 dB 90o strip-line coupler using a single oscillator (R&S Signal Generator). A cable offering 90 degree counter phase shift was also introduced to ensure injection of both magnetrons at same phase. Bandwidth of the combined injection locked magnetrons was measured to be less than 10 Hz. Power combining efficiency was achieved to be 95%. The experiment was conducted with adequate safeties in place. The procedure and safeties were counter-checked by the QC teams following appropriate QC sheets. Point recommended to be dropped.\r\n\r\n(3)   Small Scale Weapon Demonstrator. \r\n\r\n(a)   Demonstration of the irreversible damage caused on an electronic circuit through combined power of 02x 1 kW magnetrons is being planned. The experimental assembly will be housed in an aluminum casing along with proper jigs and holders for waveguide and coaxial components. CAD models of the casings and of the pertinent assemblies have been prepared. Casing to house the waveguide setup for one of the magnetrons have been developed, and its QC is in progress.\r\n\r\n(b)   Site selection for weapon demonstration is also in progress. HQ COMPAK suggested to use RDS NATHIAGALI AOR as the site vide letter No. PN/HQ COMPAK/ 03/9526808 dated 18 Jun 21. The demonstration will be conducted with adequate safeties in place, for which QC sheets are being prepared.\r\n\r\nd.   RF Power Amplifier. Three stages of the Preamplifier are required for requisite RF power input to the 100 Watt MOSFET. All stages of the preamplifier circuits have been designed. Procurement of IC and pertinent components has been completed. Design optimization of all 3 stages and their fabrication is currently in progress. Multiple manufacturing facilities have been contacted for fabrication.  \r\n\r\n2.   Following procurement actions are in progress to undertake the required experimentation.\r\n\r\na.   Procurement Completed. Procurement of following experimental components 1 kW magnetrons, coaxial circulators, coaxial terminations, Phase Locked Loop (PLL) frequency synthesizer ICs, FPGA boards, Spectrum Analyzer, Switch Mode Power Supplies, 1 kW waveguide terminations, N52 magnets, Oscilloscope, 2.5 kW waveguide terminations and DC power supply have been completed.\r\n\r\nb.   Procurement in Progress. Procurement of E-field probe, Signal Generator, replacement magnets, and high power silicon carbide material is in progress. Due COVID-19 pandemic, delay is expected in delivery of these components.\r\n\r\n3.   Following studies are being conducted to formulate research plans for combination of J-band magnetrons in the next phase: \r\na.   Research on Ceramic Materials for high power high frequency operation\r\nb.   Research on Ferrimagnetic Materials for circulators at high power and high frequency operation\r\nc.   Waveguide design requirement for high power high frequency operation\r\nd.   Design plan for RF devices\r\ne.   A 4 port X-junction circulator, based on ridged gap waveguide technology and Artificial Magnetic Conductors, has been designed capable of working at X and J band.\r\nf.   Commercial 25 kW X-band pulsed magnetrons are also being procured to study pulsed emission characteristics. Injection locking will be undertaken to furnish frequency locking requirements for pulsed magnetrons.\r\n\r\n4.   Miscellaneous Study. \r\n\r\na.   EMC/EMI Survey. Upon directions of HQ COMLOG, GM RD&TA approached NRDI R&D Wing to conduct EMC/EMI survey to finalize antenna location onboard PNS ALAMGIR vide letter number PN/PN Dockyard/PE AND D WING/ GM(RD AND  TA)/03/7895873 dated 06 Jan 21. The survey requires an E-field probe, already under procurement in project DEW (EDD Jul 21). Same probe will additionally be used for the EMC/EMI survey. \r\n\r\nb.   Testing/ Repair of Antenna Rotary Joint. The antenna rotary joint of FCR AKRAM was received for testing/repair from PN DY vide reference PN/PN DOCKYARD/W AND S Wing/ GM(W AND S)/03/9498344 dated 15 Jun 21. The received antenna was tested, dismantled and repaired in NRDI INTELL. The repaired antenna rotary joint was handed over to PN DY team. NRDI INTELL issued a detailed report, vide reference PN/DG NRDI/ R AND D Wing/03/9509171 dated 16 Jun 21, on observations of the dismantled rotary joint, the corrective actions performed and the recommendations for efficient repairs in any future occurrence of rotary joints failure. Point recommended to be dropped.\r\n\r\nc.   Testing/Qualification of Yagi-Uda antennae of SUR 17 Radar: Devised testing mechanism for Yagi-Uda Antenna array of SUR17 Radar. Antenna array was refurbished and sophisticated RF equipment was commissioned. The RADAR is currently operational with target detection range of more than 200km. Letter vide reference PN/PN DOCKYARD/W AND S WING/GM (W AND S)/03/9642437 is relevant.	DSensors	Finalized	2021-08-27 14:04:07	25	Jul 21	-20-25-	\N	f	\N
