350003	447	2021-05-28 14:07:46	\r\n1.   Following activities pertaining to in-house development and experimentation were carried out:\r\n \r\na.   Control System Designing. Point Recommended to be dropped.\r\n\r\n(1)   Control circuit PCB for phase difference detection between two magnetrons has been fabricated. The PCB will communicate the phase detection signal to Single Board Computer (SBC) through ADC. \r\n\r\n(2)   Algorithms are being developed for phase matching of two magnetrons and will be implemented on SBC.  DAC and ADC cards have been procured and tested. \r\n\r\nb.   RF Devices. Following in-house design, development and high power testing of RF devices have been completed: \r\n\r\n(1)   Waveguide circulators. Waveguide circulators equipped with biased ferrite disks and high power magnets are used in the project experimentation. Inhouse design and fabrication of 04x circulators has been completed. VNA Testing revealed satisfactory results. The fabricated circulators were also tested at 1 kW and were declared satisfactory. The circulators are successfully being used in experimentation involving injection locking and power combining of x02 1 kW magnetrons. The inhouse design and development activity resulted in a cost saving equivalent to PKR 5 Million. Point Recommended to be dropped.\r\n\r\n(2)   Waveguide directional couplers. High power testing of fabricated waveguide directional couplers has been completed. The inhouse design and development activity resulted in a cost saving equivalent to PKR 2.3 Million. Point Recommended to be dropped.\r\n\r\n(3)   Waveguide Termination. Design as well as multiphysics thermal simulation of high power waveguide termination based on wedged scheme has been completed.  Point Recommended to be dropped.\r\n\r\n(4)   Phase Shifter. IC for a 360o Phase Shifter has been procured, and the PCB has been fabricated. Testing of the phase shifter on VNA has also been completed. Point Recommended to be dropped.\r\n\r\n(5)   Power Combiner. An H-plane power combiner is required for power combination of x02 1 kW magnetrons. Inhouse design and fabrication of power combiner followed by high power testing has been successfully completed. The indigenous design and development of power combiner resulted in cost saving equivalent to PKR 0.5 Million. Point Recommended to be dropped.\r\n\r\n(6)   Horn Antenna. A high power horn antenna for 3 kW CW rating has been designed with a gain of 20 dBi. Same is being fabricated for demonstration purposes.\r\n\r\nc.   Experimentations\r\n\r\n(1)   Injection Locking of a Single Magnetron. An experimental schematic was developed to accomplish injection locking of a single magnetron. Experiments were conducted with R&S signal generator as injection source. The injection signal was fed to a free running magnetron through a series of high power circulators, and the bandwidth of the magnetron was observed to reduce within 10 Hz. Experiments have also been completed with SDR B200 as injection source. The experiment was conducted with adequate safeties in place. The procedure and safeties were counter-checked by the QC teams following appropriate QC sheets. Point Recommended to be dropped.\r\n\r\n(2)   Power Combining of x02 Magnetrons. Experimental schematic was developed to combine power of two injection locked magnetrons. The experiment has been conducted wherein power of each magnetron was fed to a waveguide combiner through series of high power circulators and directional couplers. Both magnetrons were injection locked through a 3 dB 90o strip-line coupler using a single oscillator (R&S Signal Generator). A cable offering 90 degree counter phase shift was also introduced to ensure injection of both magnetrons at same phase. Bandwidth of the combined injection locked magnetrons was measured to be less than 10 Hz. Power combining efficiency was achieved to be 95%. The experiment was conducted with adequate safeties in place. The procedure and safeties were counter-checked by the QC teams following appropriate QC sheets. Point Recommended to be dropped.\r\n\r\n(3)   Small Scale Weapon Exhibition. Demonstration of the irreversible damage caused on an electronic circuit through combined power of 02x 1 kW magnetrons is being planned. The experimental assembly will be housed in an aluminum casing along with proper jigs and holders for waveguide and coaxial components. CAD models of the casings and of the pertinent assemblies are currently being prepared. The experiment will be conducted with adequate safeties in place. The procedure and safeties will be counter-checked by the QC teams following appropriate QC sheets development.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nd.   RF Power Amplifier. \r\n\r\n(1)   In-house design optimization of 100 Watt power amplifier (PA) has been completed. Soldering of components on manufactured PCB has also been completed and required heat sink is fabricated. Point Recommended to be Dropped.\r\n\r\n(2)   QC sheets for safe testing of the designed and developed RF PA has also been prepared. Procurement of 100 Watt MOSFET has been completed. Point Recommended to be Dropped.\r\n\r\n(3)   Gate biasing circuit has been designed to ensure controlled safe testing and operation of the 100 Watt depletion mode transistor. PCB manufacturing of the same has also been completed. Point Recommended to be Dropped.\r\n\r\n(4)   Three stages of the Preamplifier are required for requisite RF power input to the 100 Watt MOSFET. All stages of the preamplifier circuits have been designed. Procurement of IC and pertinent components has been completed. Design optimization of all 3 stages and their fabrication is currently in progress. \r\n\r\n2.   Following procurement actions are in progress to undertake the required experimentation.\r\n\r\na.   Procurement Completed. Experimental components including 1 kW magnetrons, coaxial circulators, coaxial terminations, Phase Locked Loop (PLL) frequency synthesizer ICs, FPGA boards, Switch Mode Power Supplies, 1 kW waveguide terminations, N52 magnets, Oscilloscope, 2.5 kW waveguide terminations and DC power supply have been completed.\r\n\r\nb.   Procurement in Progress. Procurement of E-field probe, Spectrum Analyzer, Signal Generator, Switch Mode Power Supplies, High Power Termination (4 kW) and high power attenuators (150 W) is in progress. Due COVID-19 pandemic, delay is expected in delivery of these components.\r\n3.   Following studies are being conducted to formulate research plans for J-band in the ensuing year: \r\na.   Research on Ceramic Materials for high power high frequency operation\r\nb.   Research on Ferrimagnetic Materials for circulators at high power\r\nc.   Waveguide design requirement for high power high frequency operation\r\nd.   Design plan for RF devices\r\n\r\n4.   Miscellaneous Study. Upon directions of HQ COMLOG, GM RD&TA approached NRDI R&D Wing to conduct EMC/EMI survey to finalize antenna location onboard PNS ALAMGIR vide letter number PN/PN Dockyard/PE AND D WING/ GM(RD AND  TA)/03/7895873 dated 06 Jan 21. The survey requires an E-field probe, already under procurement in project DEW (EDD Jun 21). Same probe will additionally be used for the EMC/EMI survey.	DSensors	Edited	2021-06-15 14:51:43	25	May 21	-20-25-	\N	f	\N
350005	586	2021-12-03 09:10:26	\r\n1.   Conclusion of First Work Order. Second WO has been received, T0 will be started from 01 Dec 21. In this work order, test benches for HSTD subsystem components will be developed, ILS / documents will be handed over and ground / aerial tests will be conducted in lines with ATPs.\r\n\r\n2.   Design / Development Activities.\r\n\r\na.   MARLIN-01 UAV.  Airframe manufacturing, assembly, avionics/ control / data link integration and testing activities are completed.  Ground tests of airframe, propulsion, data link and control system are also completed.\r\n\r\nb.   MARLIN-01 Backup. Manufacturing of an additional MARLIN-01 (as backup), is in the final stages. Machining of structural parts and curing of airframe skin are completed. Assembly of airframe and avionics / control integration and painting work are also completed. In lines with the avionics system testing, a dedicated cooling system has been designed and the assembly is under progress. \r\n\r\nc.   UAV Launcher. Design and manufacturing of MARLIN-01 Launcher / pneumatic circuit testing bench are complete. Design and assembly of carriage deceleration / braking system is also completed. The designed system has been successfully tested as well. To further improve speed performance, the pneumatic actuator has been replaced with a larger stroke actuator and pulley ratio has been reduced. Testing of launcher with larger actuator is under progress.  \r\n\r\nd.   Jet Engine Testing. Bench testing of P220 Turbo jet engine (for MARLIN-01) has been conducted. Intake duct design has been improved and manufactured. Bench testing of engine with improved intake is also conducted and results are within acceptable margins. \r\n\r\ne.   Backup P220 Engine. Maiden testing of backup P220 engine (MARLIN-01 backup) is also successfully completed. Point recommended to be dropped. \r\n\r\nf.   UAV Launcher Testing.   Initial testing of launcher with integrated control system and pneumatic circuit at low and medium pressure are completed. Field testing for dead weight and dummy UAV launcher are also being planned at PN GHARO facility. Co-ordination for relevant permission is under progress.\r\n \r\ng.   Design of MARLIN-02 (full-scale HSTD). The design has been revised based on the learnings from design / manufacturing activities of MARLIN-01. Detailed design of airframe components and integration with launch / recovery systems are completed. CAD integration of avionics systems, data link, control mechanism and modifications pertaining to propulsion system are under progress. Pattern machining activities have been initiated for the completed airframe components. \r\n\r\nh.   MARLIN-02 launcher. MARLIN-02 launcher is being re-designed based on the learning from design / development of MARLIN-01 Launcher. In this regard, imperative considerations are being given to weight reduction, ease of assembly and transportation. Design of cost-effective launcher angle positioning mechanism is also completed. Export of manufacturing drawings and market surveys for COTs items are under progress. \r\n\r\nj.   Material Testing. Destructive Testing (DT) of composite material samples are being carried out using PNEC and PCSIR equipment. Tensile tests and first phase of bending tests are completed. Manufacturing process is improved in lines with the test results. Bending tests of improved samples are also completed. Testing of different composite coring materials are planned and samples are being tested to finalize MARLIN-02 coring scheme. \r\n\r\nk.   Wind Tunnel Testing. Computer Aided Design (CAD) model for development of testing model has been shared, as required by M/s DESTO.  Estimated of quotation & timeline of 190 working days is received from the firm. M/s DESTO has been requested to reduce timeline. Foreign WTT facilities are also being explored for the pertinent testing. \r\n\r\n3.   Hardware Procurement Status.\r\n\r\na.   Order is already placed for JetCat P-1000 (Germany based 1100N) turbo jet engine. Engine is ready at OEM facility while export license is being processed for shipment to Pakistan. EDD for the engine is Dec 21.\r\n\r\nb.   Veronte flight controller (of M/s Embention) excluding air antenna is received at INTELL NRDI. Individual components have been tested and radio link is established. Firmware update has also been received for tracker, which will be tested soon. Currently, development of controls for HSTD are being studied.\r\n\r\nc.   Orders are placed for raw material & COTs items for MARLIN-02 UAV and Launcher. The procurement is under progress.	DSensors	Finalized	2021-12-31 09:50:52	25	Nov 21	-20-25-	\N	f	\N
