onducted in Jun 22. Design activities are also underway for the installation of GSP onboard PNS platform. CAD models of final installation are being developed and will be completed in Jun 22.\r\n\r\n8.   Development of Test Bench. A test bench is being developed to verify the range of motion of full-scale model of GSP. Updated parameters for this design have been used in forward kinematics equations to verify the range of motion. CAD design of the model has been developed based on the calculated values. QC of design and simulation of stress and forces has also been carried out. Manufacturing of metal linkages and parts has been completed and a few remaining structural components will be completed during Jun 22. Additionally, control algorithm of test bench, which includes multiple testing protocols and extensive reporting on performance of GSP platforms is also under development. A Graphical User Interface (GUI) for ease of operator usage is also developed for GSP test bench. Testing of GUI is undertaken in lab. Complete system testing will be carried out in Jun 22 along with the developed hardware and payload.  \r\n\r\n9.   Machine Shop. Manufacturing of all parts of GSP (scaled down model, full scale model and test bench) is being carried in house. A dust collector has been designed to efficiently remove manufacturing debris from the facility and to improve operator safety. Order for dust collector has been placed and installation will be completed in Jun 22.\r\n\r\n10.   Procurement. Shortlisted stepper motors and drivers for full-scale models as well as the universal joints have also been procured. High torque motors and drivers for test bench have been received and tested in lab. Integration with hardware components is underway.\r\n\r\n11.   Lab & Field trials. Testing of full scale model of GSP is under process. For field testing, Gharo trials have been requested vide Letter no. PN/HQ NRDI/R AND D WING/03/13413611 dated 01 June 22. Approval for said trials is 