350003	683	2022-04-27 02:45:18	1.   Following activities pertaining to in-house development and experimentation were carried out:\r\n\r\na.   Small Scale Weapon Field Testing. Preliminary Field testing was of 2.5 KW setup was conducted at RDS NATHIAGALI vide reference PN/NRDI/R AND D WING/03/12427313 dated 16 Feb 22. The interference was observed with drone as target. Multiple targets such as Low Noise Amplifiers (LNAs) and Phase Frequency Detectors (PFDs) are being evaluated for disruptive demonstration. \r\n\r\nb.   Horn Antenna Improvement. Horn antenna has been redesigned and fabricated resulting in better efficiency.  A testing was carried out at SPF with one horn antenna used for transmission, and another used for reception. A 47 dBm signal was transmitted at 2.45 GHz, and 13 dBm was received at reception antenna at 10 m, resulting in propagation loss of 34 dB. The exercise was aimed to simulate the in-band damage effect on a missile seeker. The 13 dBm signal is disruptive for LNAs and PFDs used in RADAR systems of missile seekers.\r\n\r\nc.   X-Band Experiment. RF devices are being designed and fabricated at X-band for use in power combination of pulsed M1475A 25 kW magnetrons. Power supplies and pulse modulators have been procured and are undergoing extensive testing before use in experimentation.\r\n\r\n2.   RF Power Amplifier. Biasing circuit PCB has been redesigned with adequate track width suitable for high drain current. The Matching networks of the 100 Watt amplifier have been redesigned employing Simplified Real Frequency Technique (SRFT) for output MN and Bounded Performance Technique (BPT) for input MN. PCB fabrication has been completed; PCB component population is in progress and will available for testing in Apr 22.\r\n\r\n3.   Submission of Hardware Purchase Order. Hardware purchase order for experimental components for Magnetron Combination against Milestone M2 has been submitted. Point recommended to be dropped.\r\n\r\n \r\n4.   Procurement in