 of Full-Scale Model. Design of full-scale model was completed, and QC was carried out on the design. Parts were manufactured according to design and assembly has been carried out. QC of assembled parts has also been carried out. Integration of electronics in full scale model is completed. Developed algorithms have also been used to verify movement and stabilization capabilities of full scale GSP model. Integration of MOTUS IMU has been carried out in full scale model. Load testing of full scale model with antenna tracker has been carried out and performance of the platform was found satisfactory within the full operating range of the platform. Design of control electronics housing for field use is in progress. The designed housing will be IP rated and will protect electronic components from harsh sea environment, thereby ensuring optimal performance.\r\n\r\n5.   Development of Test Bench. A test bench is being developed to verify the range of motion of full-scale model of GSP. Updated parameters for this design have been used in forward kinematics equations to verify the range of motion. CAD design of the model has been developed based on the calculated values. QC of design and simulation of stress and forces have also been carried out. Manufacturing of metal linkages and parts is underway. Stepper motors and drivers for test bench have been procured. Final assembly of test bench is expected to be completed in early May 22.  Additionally, control algorithm of test bench, which includes multiple testing protocols and extensive reporting on performance of GSP platforms, has been developed. A GUI for ease of operator usage has also been developed for GSP test bench. Testing of both algorithm and GUI is underway along with hardware to verify integration and operation. A study was carried out to reduce unwanted wobbling in the platform when it is operated under load. The cause of this additional movement was determined to be the inherent freedom of movement that is available in ball joints that are used to connect linkages to the platform. Some spring dampers were used to mitigate the additional movement and the issue was resolved, thereby improving platform performance.\r\n\r\n6.   Machine Shop. Manufacturing of all parts of GSP (scaled down model, full scale model and test bench) is being carried in house. A dust collector has been designed to efficiently remove manufacturing debris from the facility and to improve operator safety. Order for dust collector has been placed and installation will be completed in May 22.\r\n\r\n7.   Procurement. Electronics components for the scaled-down model have been procured along with raw materials for structure and frame. Shortlisted stepper motors and drivers for full-scale models as well as the universal joints have also been procured. Mechanical and electrical components for test bench are being considered and procurement will be initiated once parts have been selected. Motor selection for high torque stepper motors for test bench has been completed and quotations have been obtained from vendors. Order for motors was placed and motors along with were received. Further procurement of parts for control electronics housing, raw material for manufacturing is also underway.	DSensors	Finalized	2022-06-04 04:39:42	25	Apr 22	-19-25-	\N	f	\N
