350014	686	2022-04-27 03:34:03	\r\n1.   Development of Scaled Down Model of GSP. A scaled down model of GSP has been developed in-house to validate the calculated range of motion and forces for the platform and linkages. The scaled down model has been designed to retain the full range of motion in roll ( 25?) and pitch ( 15?) as outlined in the URD, along with a capability to carry upto 1kg of payload. Electronic components for scaled down model have been procured along with raw materials for structure and frame and construction has been completed. The range of motion in roll and pitch for the system, acquired using kinematics models have been validated using the scaled down model. Development of scaled down model will provide confidence in full scale GSP development. Point recommended to be dropped.\r\n\r\n2.   Algorithm Development. The control algorithm for GSP has been extensively studied and different approaches have been implemented in Matlab. The most optimized approach in terms of system response time was observed using the inverse kinematics model along with PID. Fine tuning of parameters for PID has been carried out. Additionally, an optimized, lightweight version of algorithm to run it on industrial mini pc in the field has been developed. \r\n\r\n3.   PN Ship Visit For Finalization of Installation Option/Mechanism On-board PN Ship. Upon directions from NHQ to select feasible options shared by NRDI INTELL for installation of Ship based Line of Sight (LoS) Video Telemetry System (VTS) with Gyro Stabilized Platform (GSP), GM NCW recommended Option-1 (Portable platform) with Radome for relaying of LoS VTS vide letter no PN/PN DOCKYARD/W AND S WING/ GM (C4I)/03/12818126 dated 21 Mar 22. INTELL is pursuing the development in lines with the proposed approach. \r\n\r\n4.   Assembly of Full-Scale Model. Design of full-scale model was completed, and QC was carried out on the design. Parts were manufactured according to design and assembly has been carried out. QC of assembled parts has also been carried out. Integration of electronics in full scale model is completed. Developed algorithms have also been used to verify movement and stabilization capabilities of full scale GSP model. Integration of MOTUS IMU has been carried out in full scale model. Load testing of full scale model with antenna tracker has been carried out and performance of the platform was found satisfactory within the full operating range of the platform.\r\n\r\n5.   Development of Test Bench. A test bench is being developed to verify the range of motion of full-scale model of GSP. Updated parameters for this design have been used in forward kinematics equations to verify the range of motion. CAD design of the model has been developed based on the calculated values. QC of design and simulation of stress and forces have also been carried out. Manufacturing of metal linkages and parts is underway. Additionally, control algorithm of test bench which includes multiple testing protocols and extensive reporting on performance of GSP platforms, is also under development. A GUI for ease of operator usage is also under development for GSP test bench. A study was carried out to reduce unwanted wobbling in the platform when it is operated under load. The cause of this additional movement was determined to be the inherent freedom of movement that is available in ball joints that are used to connect linkages to the platform. Some spring dampers were used to mitigate the additional movement and the issue was resolved, thereby improving platform performance.\r\n\r\n6.   Procurement. Electronics components for the scaled-down model have been procured along with raw materials for structure and frame. Shortlisted stepper motors and drivers for full-scale models as well as the universal joints have also been procured. Mechanical and electrical components for test bench are being considered and procurement will be initiated once parts have been selected. Motor selection for high torque stepper motors for test bench has been completed and quotations have been obtained from vendors. Items are raised in minute and order will be placed as soon as approval is received.	DSensors	Finalized	2022-05-10 03:01:00	25	Apr 22	-19-25-	\N	f	\N
