350006	685	2022-04-27 21:58:24	1.   Submission of Test Benches for HSTD avionics and aerospace components. "Development of Test Benches for HSTD avionics and aerospace components" has been successfully completed and submitted against Milestone M3. \r\n\r\n2.   Design / Development Activities.\r\n\r\na.   MARLIN-01 UAV.  Airframe manufacturing, assembly, avionics/ control / data link integration is completed.  Operational tests of airframe, propulsion, data link and control system are also completed. Point recommended to be dropped \r\n\r\nb.   MARLIN-01 Backup. Manufacturing of an additional MARLIN-01 (as backup), including structural parts, skin sections, propulsion assembly, avionics assembly, avionics cooling system are completed. Ground testing is also successfully completed.\r\n\r\nc.   UAV Launcher. Design and manufacturing activities of MARLIN-01 Launcher / pneumatic circuit testing bench have been completed. Design and assembly of carriage deceleration / braking system has also been completed. The designed system has been successfully tested as well. To further improve speed performance, the pneumatic actuator has been replaced with a larger stroke actuator, the pulley ratio has been reduced and one more inlet is added to the accumulator vessel. \r\n\r\nd.   UAV Launcher Testing.   Initial testing of launcher with integrated control system and pneumatic circuit at low, medium pressure is completed. In-house testing of launcher at SPF are also completed successfully.  Field testing for dead weight and dummy UAV launches are successfully conducted at PN GHARO facility.  The criteria of projectile launch speed, aerial time and ground range are successfully met.\r\n\r\ne.   P220 Jet Engine Testing. Bench testing of P220 Turbo jet engine (for MARLIN-01) has been conducted. Intake duct design has been improved and manufactured. Bench testing of engine with improved intake is also conducted and results are within acceptable margins. \r\n\r\nf.   Backup P220 Jet Engine Testing. Maiden testing of backup P220 engine (MARLIN-01 backup) is also successfully completed.\r\n\r\ng.   P1000 Jet Engine Testing. Bench testing of P1000 Turbo jet engine (for MARLIN-02) has been conducted. Engine successfully started and thrust / temperature measurements are taken for design-adjustment of propulsion system assembly with airframe. \r\n\r\n\r\nh.   Ground Testing of Marlin-01 UAVs. Extensive ground testing activities of Marlin-01 UAVs are considered essential prior to the flight trials. In this regard: airframe load tests, pitch/roll performance testing of propulsion system, avionics endurance testing, data-link range tests, parachute release mechanism tests, control surface load tests, carriage-lock thrust testing are planned. Airframe load tests, pitch/roll performance testing of propulsion system and avionics endurance tests are successfully completed. Data link range tests and parachute release mechanism tests are partly completed. During control surface load testing, problem related to deformation of control linkages and servo failure is observed. Control linkage mechanism has been upgraded to increase stiffness and rigidity. Avionics system has been ruggedized based on root cause analysis of servo failure. Carriage-lock thrust testing of UAV has been successfully conducted at PN GHARO facility on 28th Mar 22.\r\n\r\nj.   Field / Flight Testing of Marlin-01 UAV. Field testing / launch trials of Marlin-01 UAV has been planned at PN GHARO facility in Mar 22. For this purpose, leakage testing of launcher, site survey and coordination meeting between NRDI and NSTOC reps regarding recovery of HSTD from creek area was held on 24-25 Feb 22, vide reference PN/NRDI/ R AND D Wing/03/12462317 dated 18 Feb 22. The planned field trial of UAV is successfully conducted on 28th Mar 22. During launch phase Marlin-01 endured axial load of 13g, attained the height of ~2400 ft. (735 m) and reached speed of 336 kmph (93.4 m/s). Then during ~4.5 min flight, Marlin-01 completed two rounds of 4km radius and successfully pulled multiple 5g maneuvers. Post-flight data analysis is under progress for further improvement / consolidation of full scale HSTD system. \r\n\r\nk.   Design of MARLIN-02 (full-scale HSTD). The design has been revised based on the learnings from design / manufacturing/ testing activities of MARLIN-01. Detailed design of airframe components and integration with launch / recovery systems are completed. CAD integration of avionics systems, data link, control mechanism and modifications pertaining to propulsion system are under progress. Pattern machining activities have been initiated for the completed airframe components. Pattern finishing activities and mold fabrication are also completed. Test fabrication of airframe parts in the finished molds is under progress for quality assessment and assembly tests. Subsequently, final airframe parts are being manufactured.\r\n\r\nl.   MARLIN-02 Launcher. MARLIN-02 launcher is being re-designed based on the learning from design / development of MARLIN-01 Launcher. In this regard, considerations are being given to weight reduction, ease of assembly and transportation. In order to keep the development, cost effective and reduce develop time imperative consideration is given to re-use of parts / sub-assemblies manufactured for the MARLIN-01 launcher. Export of manufacturing drawings and market surveys for COTs items are under progress. \r\n\r\nm.   Material Testing. Destructive Testing (DT) of composite material samples is being carried out using PNEC and PCSIR equipment. Tensile tests and first phase of bending tests are completed. Manufacturing process is improved in lines with the test results. Bending tests of improved samples are also completed. Testing of different composite coring materials are tested and coring scheme for MARLIN-02 has been finalized. \r\n\r\nn.   Wind Tunnel Testing. Computer Aided Design (CAD) model for development of testing model has been 