 completed. These devices will be fabricated in-house after purchasing required raw material.\r\nb.   Design of analog phase shifters required for phase matching of multiple magnetrons has been undertaken. Preliminary design study is completed. Advanced design and fabrication are currently pursued.\r\n\r\n5.   Power Amplifier. In-house design of 100W amplifier required for injection locking of magnetrons is completed. Fabrication is currently under process.\r\n\r\n6.   Anechoic Chamber. Full scale design and electromagnetic simulation of anechoic chamber is currently under consideration. Study will soon be undertaken.\r\n\r\n7.   Procurement. \r\na.   Measurement equipment including spectrum analyzer, power meters and E-field strength probe have been shortlisted. Final quotes are awaited.\r\nb.   Experimentation equipment including power attenuators, power amplifiers, water loads, coaxial and waveguide circulators, magnetron power supplies, power combiners, waveguide transitions, and waveguide launchers for magnetrons have also been shortlisted. Final quotes are awaited.	DSensors	Cancelled	2020-09-02 12:50:46	20	Jul 20	-20-25-30-20-	\N	f	\N
