350003	367	2021-03-30 11:20:12	\r\n1.   Following activities pertaining to in-house development and experimentation preparation were carried out:\r\n \r\na.   Control System Designing.\r\n\r\n(1)   The control circuit PCB for frequency locking of the injection signal source has been fabricated with requisite modifications in values of the loop filter components and OPAMP stages. The circuit board also includes an onboard microcontroller for efficient programming of the PLL IC. \r\n\r\n(2)   A new control circuit PCB for phase locking of the magnetron is being designed. The control circuit will enable phase control of the magnetron through a reference signal generator such as SDR.\r\n\r\nb.   RF Devices. Following in-house design, development and high power testing of RF devices is in progress: \r\n\r\n(1)   Waveguide circulators. Waveguide circulators equipped with biased ferrite disks and high power magnets are required in project experimentation. Fabrication of x02 circulators has been completed. VNA Testing revealed satisfactory results. The fabricated circulators were also tested at 1 kW and were declared satisfactory. The circulators are successfully being used in experimentation involving injection locking of a single 1 kW magnetron. Fabrication of x02 more circulators has been initiated which are required for injection locking of the second magnetron. \r\n\r\n(2)   Waveguide directional couplers. High power testing of waveguide directional couplers has been completed. Fabrication of x04 directional couplers have been completed. \r\n\r\n(3)   Waveguide Termination. Design as well as multiphysics thermal simulation of high power waveguide termination based on wedged scheme has been completed. \r\n\r\n(4)   Phase Shifter. IC for a 360o Phase Shifter has been procured, and the PCB has been fabricated. Testing of the phase shifter on VNA is in progress.\r\n\r\n(5)   Power Combiner. An H-plane power combiner is required for power combination of x02 1 kW magnetrons. Design of the power combiner is completed and multiphysics analysis is in progress. \r\n\r\nc.   Experimentations.\r\n\r\n(1)   High Power Testing of RF Devices. Testing of the in-house developed circulators and directional couplers has been completed at 1 kW. All RF devices performed satisfactorily at 1 kW. \r\n\r\n(2)   Injection Locking of a Single Magnetron. An experimental scheme was developed to accomplish injection locking of single magnetron. Experiments have been conducted with RF signal generator as injection source. The injection signal was fed to a free running magnetron through series of high power circulators. The bandwidth of the magnetron was observed to reduce within 10 Hz. Similar experiments will be planned with SDRs as injection sources, at different power levels. This will offer selection of an efficient injection source.\r\n\r\nd.   RF Power Amplifier. \r\n\r\n(1)   QC checks for safe testing of the designed and developed RF PA has also been completed. \r\n\r\n(2)   Procurement of IC and pertinent components along with fabrication of PCBs for 100 Watt MOSFET is completed.\r\n\r\n3.   Following procurement actions are in progress to undertake the required experimentation.\r\n\r\na.   Procurement Completed. Procurement of switch mode power supplies, waveguide terminations and DC power supply have been completed.\r\n\r\nb.   Procurement in Progress. Procurement of waveguide terminations required for injection locking of the second magnetron, E-field probe and Oscilloscope is in progress. Due COVID-19 pandemic, delay is expected in delivery of these components.	DSensors	Edited	2021-04-27 09:24:46	25	Mar 21	-20-25-	\N	f	\N
