350003	427	2021-05-05 09:35:28	1.   Following activities pertaining to in-house development and experimentation were carried out:\r\n \r\na.   Control System Designing.\r\n\r\n(1)   Control circuit PCB for phase difference detection between two magnetrons has been fabricated. The PCB will communicate the phase detection signal to Single Board Computer (SBC) through ADC. \r\n\r\n(2)   Algorithms are being developed for phase matching of two magnetrons and will be implemented on SBC.  DAC and ADC cards have been procured and tested. \r\n\r\nb.   RF Devices. Following in-house design, development and high power testing of RF devices have been completed: \r\n\r\n(1)   Waveguide circulators. Waveguide circulators equipped with biased ferrite disks and high power magnets are used in the project experimentation. In house design and fabrication of 04x circulators has been completed. VNA Testing revealed satisfactory results. The fabricated circulators were also tested at 1 kW and were declared satisfactory. The circulators are successfully being used in experimentation involving injection locking and power combining of x02 1 kW magnetrons. The inhouse design and development activity resulted in a cost saving equivalent to PKR 5 Million. \r\n\r\n(2)   Waveguide directional couplers. High power testing of fabricated waveguide directional couplers has been completed. The inhouse design and development activity resulted in a cost saving equivalent to PKR 2.3 Million.\r\n\r\n(3)   Waveguide Termination. Design as well as multiphysics thermal simulation of high power waveguide termination based on wedged scheme has been completed.  Point recommended to be dropped.\r\n\r\n(4)   Phase Shifter. IC for a 360o Phase Shifter has been procured, and the PCB has been fabricated. Testing of the phase shifter on VNA has also been completed.\r\n\r\n(5)   Power Combiner. An H-plane power combiner is required for power combination of x02 1 kW magnetrons. Inhouse design and fabrication of power combiner followed by high power testing has been successfully completed. The indigenous design and development of power combiner resulted in cost saving equivalent to PKR 0.5 Million. \r\n\r\n\r\nc.   Experimentations.\r\n\r\n(1)   Injection Locking of a Single Magnetron. An experimental schematic was developed to accomplish injection locking of a single magnetron. Experiments were conducted with R&S signal generator as injection source. The injection signal was fed to a free running magnetron through a series of high power circulators, and the bandwidth of the magnetron was observed to reduce within 10 Hz. Experiments have also been completed with SDR B200 as injection source. The experiment was conducted with adequate safeties in place. The procedure and safeties were counter-checked by the QC teams following appropriate QC sheets.\r\n\r\n(2)   Power Combining of x02 Magnetrons. Experimental schematic was developed to combine power of two injection locked magnetrons. The experiment has been conducted wherein power of each magnetron was fed to a waveguide combiner through series of high power circulators and directional couplers. Both magnetrons were injection locked through a 3 dB 90o strip-line coupler using a single oscillator (R&S Signal Generator). A cable offering 90 degree counter phase shift was also introduced to ensure injection of both magnetrons at same phase. Bandwidth of the combined injection locked magnetrons was measured to be less than 10 Hz. Power combining efficiency was achieved to be 95%. The experiment was conducted with adequate safeties in place. The procedure and safeties were counter-checked by the QC teams following appropriate QC sheets.\r\n\r\nd.   RF Power Amplifier. \r\n\r\n(1)   In-house design optimization of 100 Watt power amplifier (PA) has been completed. Soldering of components on manufactured PCB has also been completed. The required heat sink has been designed and fabrication is in progress. \r\n\r\n(2)   QC sheets for safe 