350002	148	2020-08-08 15:44:40	1.   Reactive Jamming. The reactive jamming software code is finalized for effective detection and tracking of fast and slow moving UAVs.\r\n\r\n2.   GPS Spoofing\r\na.   HOTAS Controlled GPS Spoofing. The counterfeit signals for 7 different directions i.e. left, right, forward, backward, up, down and center location are controlled using the Hands On Throttle And Stick (HOTAS). Using this controller, the operator can alter the GPS signal in any direction depending upon sighting of hostile UAV in real time. The alteration in GPS signal force the UAV to traverse the spoofed/ disrupted path.  \r\nb.   Internet Independent Spoofing (IIS). A procedure is formulated for implementing GPS spoofing at remote sites where internet is not available\r\n1)   Gathering of real time Ephemeris data of 10-12 satellites without internet is a challenge. \r\n2)   A capability is developed to predict the Ephemeris data for the spoofing attack accurately using GPS data, received using GPS receivers, up to 24 hours before the spoofing attack. \r\nc.   Upon receipt of 3D X-Band RADAR, target UAV tracking is possible enabling automated generation of required GPS signals capable to traverse the UAV to spoofed/ disrupted path. \r\nd.   Force Majeure has been invoked by DITD due COVID pandemic. The delivery of 3D X-Band RADAR is also delayed due to export permit processing delays caused by COVID 19 pandemic. Once 3D X-band RADAR will be received, 8-10 weeks are required for customization and testing of GPS spoofing milestone.\r\n3.   Housing of Project Eagle Hunt equipment in Marinized Container will be used as Technology demonstrator.\r\n\r\na.   The planning for housing the spoofing and jamming equipment onboard marinized container is finalized. The INTELL team along with all the received equipment will move to the facility of M/s RIMS on 17th August 2020 for the installation of equipment.\r\n\r\n1)   Direction finding antenna,  RADAR, jamming and spoofing anten